./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:91:| CCS-003 | Implement `SampleLibrary` on-disk store backed by `index.sqlite` with tag/source/pitch/mood-range queries. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleLibrary(root: Path)` opens / creates `index.sqlite` with table `samples` carrying every `SampleRecord` field plus full-text-search index on `character_tags`<br/>- `library.add(record)` persists row + verifies file presence<br/>- `library.find(source=, character_any=, character_all=, pitch_band=, arc_phase=, mood_range=, limit=)` returns ordered list (most recent first within match set)<br/>- tests cover insert, query by each filter, empty-result path, and corrupted-DB rebuild |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:93:| CCS-005 | Implement `SampleSelector` mood/mode/arc-aware picker with deterministic seed-based selection within match set. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleSelector(library, rng_seed: int)` exposes `select(mode: ArtistMode, arc_phase: str, mood: Mapping[str,float], target_character: tuple[str,...] = (), avoid_recent: int = 5) -> SampleRecord \| None`<br/>- selection prefers samples with matching `arc_phase` and overlapping mood (dot-product over energy/valence/arousal); falls back to character_tags only; falls back to library random within source-source preference per-mode<br/>- `avoid_recent` excludes the N most-recently-played samples (per-mode rolling window)<br/>- per-mode source preference: solitary→[self,contact,room,library]; companion→[library,self,room]; working_ambience→[room,library]; evening_reflection→[self,library,theramini]; storm→[contact,library,room]<br/>- selection is deterministic given (library state, rng_seed, kwargs)<br/>- tests verify per-mode preference order, mood-overlap ranking, avoid_recent, deterministic replay |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:97:| CCS-009 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:98:| CCS-010 | Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py` exposes `BufferPool(scsynth_client, capacity=64)` with `acquire(record) -> bufnum`, `release(record)`, `evict_lru()`<br/>- WAV file path → `/b_allocRead bufnum path 0 -1` over OSC<br/>- LRU eviction triggered automatically when `acquire` exceeds capacity<br/>- on scsynth restart, pool detects buffer-id reuse failure and rebuilds<br/>- tests with a mock OSC client verify allocate, evict, release, and reuse paths |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:99:| CCS-011 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:100:| CCS-012 | Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. | MUST | T1 | - `dispatch_sample(record, intent, *, position, position_rate, grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose, amp, fx_send) -> SamplerHandle` issues `/b_allocRead` (if needed), `/s_new sw_sampler ...` and returns a handle for later `/n_set gate 0` release<br/>- correlates `record.gain_db` with `amp`<br/>- handles per-mode effects presets (delay_time / verb_mix / freeze / comb_b vary by mode)<br/>- tests with mock OSC client verify correct bundle ordering, gate-release path, and per-mode preset application |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:103:| CCS-015 | Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. | MUST | T1 | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:104:| CCS-016 | Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::InterestingMomentDetector` pulls 1-second windows every 250 ms<br/>- flags a window when: `spectral_flux > 0.6 * recent_median` AND `rms > -45 dBFS` AND `transient_count >= 2` AND `since_last_capture > 30 sec`<br/>- on flag, expands to a 4–8 second window centered on the flagged sub-window (length proportional to spectral richness)<br/>- thresholds are tunable via env / config<br/>- tests with canned audio fixtures (silence, footsteps, dishwasher hum, music) verify expected flag/no-flag for each |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:107:| CCS-019 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:109:| CCS-021 | Implement TDD-grade test fixtures with canned 1-second audio windows representing each detector branch (silence, footsteps, dishwasher, music, dogs, transient cluster) for fast deterministic CI. | MUST | T1 | - `my-claw/tests/fixtures/sample_capture/` directory with WAV fixtures<br/>- `test_sample_capture_daemon.py` exercises each fixture against the detector and asserts expected flag<br/>- fixtures are short (≤2 s) and committed to repo so CI does not need real JACK<br/>- documented as the way to add new detector cases |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:117:| CCS-029 | Implement `metrics::sampler_event_count_per_piece` and `metrics::sampler_library_vs_self_ratio` for the metrics-CI gate. | MUST | T1 | - integrated with the existing render `metrics.py` (CCH-014)<br/>- per-piece event count is recorded and surfaced in operator diagnostics<br/>- library:self ratio is computed across the last 50 pieces; healthy band 1.5..3.0<br/>- tests verify metric computation and threshold reporting |
./my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:118:| CCS-030 | Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). | MUST | T1 | - integrated into `render/antipatterns.py` (CCH-015)<br/>- `sampler_dominating` fires per-piece, surfaces in metrics gate as warning (downgrade to MUST FIX after 3 consecutive)<br/>- `sampler_silent_quintet_member` fires across rolling window of last 50 pieces; mode-weighted means the threshold scales with `sampler_density` per mode (so working_ambience never trips it)<br/>- tests verify each detector with synthetic piece histories |
