./my-claw/sdp/prd-agent-runtime-substrate.md:54:| RTS-002 | Implement a persistent shell/session abstraction for shell-backed work. It must support serial command queueing, current-directory tracking, timeouts, graceful interruption, and restart when the shell dies. | MUST | T2 | - Commands can execute in the same live shell<br/>- `cd` persists within session scope<br/>- Timeout and cancel terminate child processes cleanly<br/>- Dead shell auto-restarts without corrupting caller state |
